Program: The Forum
Title: Radioactivity: Friend or Foe?
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p040bc8n
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 13 Jul 2016
One of the first things that comes to mind when thinking of radioactivity is often a nuclear accident or dangerous rays. But radioactivity is in fact a much more varied phenomenon, one that can bring us great benefits as well as put us in danger. With help from three experts, Rajan Datar looks for a more nuanced picture of the role radioactivity plays in our lives. Photo: A symbol for radioactivity is visible on a radioactively-contaminated container. (Getty Images) Show less